<div id="review_189289306" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/189289306" />
    <a title="Annette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3110122-annette"><img alt="Annette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1262842797p2/3110122.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/189289306?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annette" href="/user/show/3110122-annette">Annette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer189289306" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12943592655067979187">Another great book from Elizabeth George! Lots of plot twists and many candidates as suspects in the double murder! George writes with a lot of British slang and local jargon, so it takes a while to &quot;get into&quot; her style of writing. But doing that adds so much depth to the characters and it also endears them to the reader.<br/><br/>One bit that lacked for me was I wanted to see a conclusion to the Broughton Manor story, i.e., the relationship between Julian and his cousin Samantha. Also, did Jeremy give up</span>
  <span id="freeText12943592655067979187" style="display:none">Another great book from Elizabeth George! Lots of plot twists and many candidates as suspects in the double murder! George writes with a lot of British slang and local jargon, so it takes a while to "get into" her style of writing. But doing that adds so much depth to the characters and it also endears them to the reader.<br /><br />One bit that lacked for me was I wanted to see a conclusion to the Broughton Manor story, i.e., the relationship between Julian and his cousin Samantha. Also, did Jeremy give up drinking? We don't know.<br /><br />Thomas Lynley was a prig in this one, but as he is the main character in the series, we're seeing his rather human side. I guess he can't be perfect all the time. I love his wife Helen.<br /><br />I enjoyed reading about Barbara Havers. There was much of her in this episode. I love that she is the opposite of Lynley. Where Lynley is polished and good looking, Havers is homely and dumpy. She is definitely rough around the edges and I like that contrast.<br /><br />Thanks, Liz!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12943592655067979187" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


