              <span id="reviewTextContainer2667370529" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11575419000045377432">Somewhere between 3 and 4*, compared to the previous one (#9). I found the storyline too confusing, too many possible suspects for the murders I think. Nicki&apos;s father, mother, lovers (at least 3), ex-employer, baddies pursued by father when in SO10, would-be girlfriend of one of the lovers plus at least one other character..... Whilst cleverly done, there were more than a few moments when I just wanted the swirl to stop and the story to make progress.<br/><br/>On the character side of things - Havers cont</span>
  <span id="freeText11575419000045377432" style="display:none">Somewhere between 3 and 4*, compared to the previous one (#9). I found the storyline too confusing, too many possible suspects for the murders I think. Nicki's father, mother, lovers (at least 3), ex-employer, baddies pursued by father when in SO10, would-be girlfriend of one of the lovers plus at least one other character..... Whilst cleverly done, there were more than a few moments when I just wanted the swirl to stop and the story to make progress.<br /><br />On the character side of things - Havers continues to be the terrier, intent on her own version of the facts. Love her! I am beginning to remember how irritating Lynley's continued internal musings about how he struggles with personal relationships could be! Enjoyed seeing Nkata taking a broader role - my mental images of him struggling with some of the aspects of Nicki's work were hilarious.</span>
